te<-read.table("GCF_002938485.1_Soryzae_2.0_genomic.fna.align.parseRM.all-repeats.tab")
names(te)<-c("TEname", "Class", "SF", "length", "frags", "copies", "bp", "DIV", "DIV-na", "DEL", "DEL-na","INS", "INS-na","Avgbpmasked","perc")
head(te)

“bp” is out of Aurelie’s script and do resolve overlaps towards the youngest insertion

FIG1A

library(ggplot2)
library(scales) # allows comma instead of scientific notation
te$spam=rep("spam", length(te$TEname)) # need to make x axis

#barplot + custom genome size background
ggplot(te,
       aes(x = spam, y = bp/1000000, fill = forcats::fct_rev(Class)))+
  geom_col(width = 1)+
  annotate("rect", ymin = sum(te$bp/1000000), ymax = GS/1000000, xmin = 0.5, xmax = 1.5, fill = "beige")+
  scale_fill_manual(values = rev(c("salmon", "royalblue", "green3", "yellow", "orange", "black")))+
  coord_flip()+
  scale_x_discrete(labels = "So2 assembly")+
  scale_y_continuous(label=comma, limits = c(0,1000))+
  xlab("")+
  #ylim(0,1000)+
  ylab("Genome size (Mb)")+
  theme(panel.background = element_blank())

FIG1D

#remove Sat and simple reps
tete<-te[te$Class != "Satellite" & te$Class!="Simple_repeat",]
#order by Class
tete<-tete[order(tete$Class),]
#group per Class
tete$CSD<-paste(tete$Class,tete$SF, sep = "-")
#get sum per SF in each Class
tete.s<-as.data.frame(sort(tapply(tete$bp, tete$CSD, sum)))
#reformat
tete.s$CSF<-rownames(tete.s)
library(tidyr)
tete.s$CSsplit<-tete.s$CSF
tete.s<-tete.s %>% separate(CSsplit, c("Class", "SF"), sep="-")
names(tete.s)<-c("totalbp", "CSF", "Class", "SF")
#final ordering
tete.s<-tete.s[order(tete.s$Class, tete.s$totalbp, decreasing = T),]

SUP FIG (coorelation TE% x copy equivalent)

The “copy equivalent” or cp_eq is calculated as follow: cp_eq = total bp masked (non-redundant) / consensus length

# compute cp equivalents
tete$cp_eq=tete$bp/tete$length
# plot
ggplot(tete)+
  geom_point(aes(x = cp_eq, y = bp/GS*100, col = Class), alpha = .25, shape = 16)+
  scale_y_log10(labels = comma)+
  scale_x_log10()+
  facet_wrap(~Class, ncol = 4)+
  scale_color_manual(values = rev(c("grey50", "lightblue", "black", "green3", "royalblue", "salmon")))+
  xlab("copy equivalent")+
  ylab("percent genome")+
  theme(panel.background = element_blank())
